
[1]pervert

   PERVERT', v.t. [L. perverto; per and verto, to turn.]

   1. To turn from truth, propriety, or from its proper purpose; to
   distort from its true use or end; as, to pervert reason by misdirecting
   it; to pervert the laws by misinterpreting and misapplying them; to
   pervert justice; to pervert the meaning of an author; to pervert
   nature; to pervert truth.

   2. To turn from the right; to corrupt.

   He in the serpent had perverted Eve.
